    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2011 BMW M3 Coupe, a definitive example of the high-revving S65 naturally aspirated 4.0L V8 era. This power plant features eight individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering 414 hp with an 8,400 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a tactile 6-speed manual transmission and a Variable M Differential Lock for optimal torque distribution. This specimen is in concours-level condition; the factory paint retains its original depth and the chassis shows no signs of subframe stress. Crucially, the rod bearings have been proactively replaced with treated shells and ARP bolts, and the throttle actuators have been uprated to ensure mechanical longevity. The interior is preserved in original Novillo leather, free from bolster wear or UV degradation. A mechanically synchronized, turn-key masterpiece for the purist collector.",
